    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe [`textDocument/inlayHint` response](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#inlayHint) optionally contains text edits. [`basedpyright`](https://github.com/DetachHead/basedpyright/blob/65d8d73f0d3c427064688d8f8cf3b6a808a0fd42/packages/pyright-internal/src/languageService/inlayHintsProvider.ts#L36) use this field to provide python type annotations and kwargs that can be inserted into the buffer. There's no existing APIs in `vim.lsp.inlay_hint` that make it convenient for users to insert these edits.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nProvide a `vim.lsp.inlay_hint.apply_text_edits` function that can be used for creating keymaps, so that users can conveniently insert the hints.\n\nI have a working implementation here: https://github.com/Davidyz/inlayhint-filler.nvim\nI can open a PR to upstream this if the maintainers are ok with it. (Actually, it's probably better to slim it down if it's upstreamed, because some of the options aren't standard LSP stuff, like the `force` option, which enforces the insert even if there's no `textEdits`)",
