            "body": "The thing is, the current `vim.lsp.inlay_hint` module uses the built-in handler, which can be overwritten by users/plugins (see https://github.com/chrisgrieser/nvim-lsp-endhints/issues/15). I originally did use the `vim.lsp.inlay_hint.get` to fetch the hints, but it'll break if the customised handlers do not preserve the text edits correctly. Having a custom handler in the `apply_text_edits` function will make it more robust.",
